metadata.description:
The End 

 The End displays a rolling credit sequence, rewriting the labels of individuals involved in art history and highlighting the potential impact of AI on the art world. The piece invites audiences to consider the implications of the integration of AI in art production and the end of human-created art. Through its nuanced interplay between art historical and cinematic references, The End stands as a powerful meditation on the ontology of artistic authorship in the age of automation.

 Edition of 3 + 1 ap. 

 Edition 2
